URSUS SIEM — Licensing model
============================

URSUS SIEM is split into three editions; this LICENSE file applies to the
Community edition (the contents of this repository).

* Community edition  — AGPL-3.0-or-later (this file)
* Compliance edition — proprietary; commercial license required
* Pro edition        — proprietary; commercial license required

The compliance & pro modules are shipped as separately-licensed plugins
loaded at runtime; they do not modify or relink the Community core.


                    GNU AFFERO GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE
                       Version 3, 19 November 2007

 Copyright (C) 2007 Free Software Foundation, Inc. <https://fsf.org/>
 Everyone is permitted to copy and distribute verbatim copies of this
 license document, but changing it is not allowed.

[Full AGPL-3.0 text omitted for brevity here — the canonical version
 is at https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.txt and SHOULD be inserted
 verbatim before any public release. CI verifies the hash matches.]

Why AGPL-3.0
------------

We pick AGPL-3.0 (not MIT/Apache) so:
  * SaaS forks must disclose their modifications.
  * Dual-licensing into Compliance/Pro stays meaningful as a moat.
  * The Community tier remains a real, full-featured SIEM the small
    business can adopt without contractual encumbrance.

Compliance & Pro editions
-------------------------

The Compliance edition adds, under a commercial license:
  * Pre-tuned SIGMA rule packs for ФСТЭК / 152-ФЗ
  * PDF report templates for Приказ №21, №31, КИИ 187-ФЗ
  * Premium Threat-Intelligence feeds (Recorded Future, Mandiant, …)
  * Signed update channel

The Pro edition adds, additionally:
  * On-prem LLM (logvault-llm) with NL→PDQL and incident narrative
  * EDR-light agent extensions (process / USB / file integrity)
  * Multi-tenant SaaS controls
  * Helm chart for kubernetes deployments
  * Priority support and assistance with ФСТЭК certification

Contributing
------------

Contributions to the Community edition are accepted under AGPL-3.0.
By submitting a PR you certify that your contribution is your own work
and you have the right to license it under AGPL-3.0.
